article.description: — Lamar Norman Jr. had 19 points and seven rebounds as Western Michigan beat Akron 61-57 in overtime on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Norman Jr. lifts W. Michigan over Akron 61-57 in OT
article.linkText: Norman Jr. lifts W. Michigan over Akron 61-57 in OT
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- — Lamar Norman Jr. had 19 points and seven rebounds as Western Michigan beat Akron 61-57 in overtime on Tuesday night. Mileek McMillan had 14 points and nine rebounds for Western Michigan (6-20, 2-13 Mid-American Conference). Markeese Hastings added 11 rebounds. Akron totaled 21 points in the second half, a season low for the team. Enrique Freeman had 16 points, 18 rebounds and five blocks for the Zips (16-8, 9-5). Xavier Castaneda added 11 points. Ali Ali, the Zips' leading scorer heading into the contest at 14 points per game, was held to five points on 1-for-10 shooting. The Broncos leveled the season series against the Zips. Akron defeated Western Michigan 74-73 on Jan. 18. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
